1. Tools

In order to make a good develop and use all the tools in the developmen, we use Google Chrome.

In order to install Google Chrome in Debian/Ubuntu

Install Google Chrome on Debian 10
--------------------------------------------
Download the version for the system from:

https://www.google.com/chrome/fast-and-secure/

sudo dpkg -i google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.deb


Install Google Chorme in windows 10
-------------------------------------
Just search with name "Download Google Chorme"

Select our plattform and begin the download.

Execute the installer and enjoy it!


Install Visual Studio Code
----------------------------

Visual Studio Code is a lightweight but powerful source code editor which runs on your desktop and is available for Windows, macOS and Linux. It comes with built-in support for JavaScript, TypeScript and Node.js and has a rich ecosystem of extensions for other languages (such as C++, C#, Java, Python, PHP, Go) and runtimes (such as .NET and Unity).

This editor lets build and integrate the development, debugging and add extensions.

In Google we'll search "Download Visual Studio Code"

or in the Oficial Site:

https://code.visualstudio.com/download

It's an multiplatform tool, we can work with Linux, Windows or Mac

Direct Link:
https://code.visualstudio.com/sha/download?build=stable&os=linux-deb-x64

Reference:
https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/?dv=linux64_deb


Work with Visual Studio Code
----------------------------
we use Dark Theme

Seeting > Color Theme 
	Light (Default Color)


Install Sublime Text
----------------------
cd Downloads/
wget -c https://download.sublimetext.com/sublime-text_build-3211_amd64.deb

dpkg -i sublime-text_build-3211_amd64.deb


If we Use Ubuntu we can install Atom 

Install Atom, subllime and Brackets
--------------------------------------
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/atom
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install atom

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/brackets
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install brackets

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/sublime-text-3
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install sublime-text-installer

References:
https://www.sublimetext.com/3


In especific you are free to work as you wish


